==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Putredinous
<hw>Pu*tred"i*nous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>putredo</ets> rottenness, fr. <ets>putrere</ets> to be rotten. See
<er>Putrid</er>.]</ety> <def>Proceeding from putrefaction, or partaking
of the putrefactive process; having an offensive smell; stinking;
rotten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Putrefaction</ent>⟦br⟧
